  "texts": [
    "Informally, this can be understood as the property that the extractor output bits are near-perfect, even conditioned on the input Y.By convention, we will always assume that the extractor is strong in the (weak) seed, although the role of the input sources can usually be exchanged for two-source extractors.",
    "All extractors presented in this work are strong with the same error and output length.",
    "Having this additional property leads to some useful consequences:1.",
    "Y may become known to the adversary without compromising the security of the extractor output, i.e.",
    "the extractor output remains ϵ-perfectly random.2."
  ],
